verbose_text: DAO increased significantly from beginning of surgery to POD1 in the CON group (2.49 +/- 0.41 ng/mL vs 3.47 +/- 0.50 ng/mL vs 4.48 +/- 0.94 ng/mL, P = 0.028, Fig. XREF_FIG A), whereas no significant increase was observed in the DEX group (2.30 +/- 0.22 ng/mL vs 2.27 +/- 0.25 ng/mL vs 2.71 +/- 0.39 ng/mL, P = 0.25, Fig. XREF_FIG A).
evidence: DAO increased significantly from beginning of surgery to POD1
